<div class="container">
  <div class="display-4">CPT Report</div>
  <p><strong>Test Date: </strong><%= userScore.date %></p>
  <%- include('../profile/profile.details.ejs.ejs', { user }) %>
  <p class="lead">
    The Theory of Multiple suggests that each individual possesses at least
    eight relatively independent mental abilities or intelligences. Career
    Preference Test (CPT) emphasizes identifying a person’s areas of strength
    and then using this information as the basis for career preference choices.
    Understanding your CPT Profile can help you identify a career focus and
    begin your career planning and exploration process.
  </p>

  <div class="d-flex flex-column align-items-center my-3">
    <canvas id="<%= userScore._id %>"></canvas>
    <button class="btn btn-primary no-print" id="save_0">Save as Image</button>
  </div>

    <%- include('../profile/scripts/createBarChart.ejs', {
        userScore,
        getChartData,
        scoreIndex: 0
    }) %>

    <p>Besides your top 3 intelligences, if your score for any intelligence is above 60%, you’re probably using that intelligence quite often to help you learn. Refer to the table below for a detailed description of each of your dominant intelligence.
    </p>

   <table class="table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th scope="col">#</th>
          <th scope="col">Intelligence Type</th>
          <th scope="col">Intelligence Description</th>
          <th scope="col">Sample Careers</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <th scope="row">1</th>
          <td>Verbal-Linguistic</td>
          <td>Words and language, written and spoken; retention, interpretation and explanation of ideas and information.</td>
          <td>• Editors, linguists, translators • PR consultants, media consultants • TV and radio presenters, voice-over artistes • Lawyer– legal assistant – comedian –historian • Interpreter – journalist – lawyer – librarian • Manager – novelist –
            orator – philosopher • Writers -play writer– poet – politician – proofreader </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th scope="row">2</th>
          <td>Logical-Mathematical</td>
          <td>Logical thinking, detecting patterns, scientific reasoning and deduction; analyze problems, perform mathematical calculations.</td>
          <td>• Scientists, engineers, computer experts • Accountants, statisticians, researchers, analysts • Traders, bankers’, • Bookmakers, insurance brokers, • Negotiators, dealmakers, trouble-shooters, directors • Investment broker - lawyer •
            Biologist - chemist - microbiologist - pharmacist - physician </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th scope="row">3</th>
          <td>Visual-Spatial</td>
          <td>Visual and spatial perception; interpretation and creation of visual images.</td>
          <td>• Artists, designers, cartoonists, story-boarders • Architects, photographers, sculptors, town-planners • Engineers, cosmetics and beauty consultants. • Photographer - graphic designer • Advertiser - architect - artist - builder -
            carpenter • Chess player - commercial artist • Computer specialist - craftsperson - decorator - dentist </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th scope="row">4</th>
          <td>Musical</td>
          <td>Musical ability, awareness, appreciation and use of sound.</td>
          <td>• Musicians, singers, composers • DJ's, music producers • Piano tuners, acoustic engineers • Entertainers, party-planners • Environment and noise advisors, voice coaches • Conductor - composer - band member - choir director </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th scope="row">5</th>
          <td>Bodily-Kinesthetic</td>
          <td>Body movement control, manual dexterity, physical agility and balance; eye and body coordination.</td>
          <td> • Dancers, demonstrators, actors • Athletes, divers, sportsperson • Soldiers, fire-fighters • Fishermen, crafts-people • Gardeners, chefs • Acupuncturists, healers, adventurers • Acrobat - aerobic teacher - coach • Physical education
            teacher - athlete - ballet dancer </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th scope="row">6</th>
          <td>Interpersonal</td>
          <td>Perception of other people's feelings; ability to relate to others; interpretation of behavior and communications</td>
          <td>• Therapists, HR professionals, mediators • Leaders, counselors, politicians, educators • Sales-people • Clergy, psychologists, teachers • Doctors, healers, organizers, advertising professionals • Coaches and mentors • Travel
            agent/counselor • Business person - child care worker </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th scope="row">7</th>
          <td>Intrapersonal</td>
          <td>Self-awareness, personal cognizance, personal objectivity, the capability to understand oneself, one's relationship to others and the world, and one's own reaction to change.</td>
          <td>• Entrepreneur - consultant - counselor - creative writer • Guru - leadership trainer - philosopher - psychiatrist • Psychologist - psychotherapist - researcher - sage • Self employed people - spiritual counselor - therapist • Writer
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th scope="row">8</th>
          <td>Naturalistic</td>
          <td>Understanding the natural world of plants and animals, noticing their characteristics, and categorizing them.</td>
          <td>• Forest rangers, nature guides • Animal trainers, zoo keepers • Landscape designers, gardeners • Scientists investigating the biological and physical worlds • Bird watchers, veterinarians, farmers • People involved in scouting and
            camping </td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
</div>

